Arsenal midfielder Santi Cazorla is among
number of players to have offered support to Villarreal defender Mateo Musacchio following his gruesome leg injury
The Argentinian fractured his fibula and dislocated his left ankle during his side 's 1-1 draw at Getafe in the Primera Division on Sunday
No recovery time has been set by the club but Musacchio is expected to be sidelined for at least six months
Santi Cazorla played with Musacchio for Villarreal before joining Arsenal
